		<div class="entry-wrapper">
			
				<div class="cat-links ">
					<a href="https://calmatters.org/category/environment/climate-change/">Climate Change</a>				</div>
				<h3 class="entry-title"><a href="https://calmatters.org/environment/climate-change/2024/03/california-climate-change-mandate-analysis/" rel="bookmark">California isn’t on track to meet its climate change mandates — and a new analysis says it’s not even close</a></h3>										<div class="entry-meta">
											<span class="byline">
							<span class="author-prefix">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://calmatters.org/author/alejandro-lazo/">Alejandro Lazo</a></span>						</span><!-- .author-name -->
										</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					</div><!-- .entry-wrapper -->
	</article>

				</div>
		
	</div>
	
<p>The main obstacle to government action at the scale this crisis demands are corporate polluters as one of the biggest financial spenders on elections and lobbying in California. The <a href="https://envirovoters.org/scorecard/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">California Environmental Scorecard</a> started tracking legislators that accept money from Big Oil at the turn of the decade. </p>
<aside>			<div class="newspack-popup-container newspack-popup newspack-inline-popup newspack-lightbox-no-border" role="button" tabindex="0" style="background-color:#FFFFFF;color:#000" id="id_447644" data-segments="" data-frequency="0,0,0,month">
				
